  "text": "The relations between the coordinates of the space may affect the properties of the physical system. For a multipartite system, there maybe some new correlations between the subsystems induced by the noncommutativity of the space, such as entanglement or other types of quantum correlations. Quantum entanglement is one of the key features of quantum physics, and it has many applications in quantum information and many-body physics to spacetime physics [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . Entropy provides a tool that can be used to quantify entanglement. If the overall system is pure, the entropy of one subsystem can be used to measure its degree of entanglement with the other subsystems. This is the so-called entanglement entropy. Some authors have already studied the quantum entanglement and entropy of physical systems in noncommutative space [CITATION_3] - [CITATION_4] .",
